How to Run the Application
Requirements
Python 3.8 or higher

No external libraries required

How to Run (Test Stage)
Open a terminal or command prompt.

Navigate to the project root directory (where pet_rock_genie.py and README.md are located):

Example: cd /path/to/PetRockGenie

Run the application using Python:

python pet_rock_genie.py

or, if your entry file is named main.py:

python main.py

Confirm that the startup banner shows the Test Environment – Version 2.0.0 identity.

At the prompt, type any yes/no question and press Enter.

If you forget a question mark, the app will display a tip suggesting that questions usually end with ?.

If you press Enter on an empty line, the app will remind you to enter a question.

To exit the Test Stage cleanly, type one of the exit commands and press Enter:

quit

exit

bye

On exit, the application reports how many questions were asked during the session and writes the interaction details to pet_rock_genie_v2.log in the project directory.

Test Environment Notes
This release is deployed to the Test Stage as part of the software promotion workflow for this course. The goals of the Test Stage for Version 2 include:

Validating enhanced logging behavior.

Ensuring user input handling functions correctly.

Verifying backward compatibility with Version 1 behavior.

Confirming improvements do not alter the expected application flow.


